task.summary: Default task

Version 1.0.0
- Let's pretend this hasn't been released yet - Major overhaul to the trail effects, they're now smooth and don't cause lag issues

Version 1.0.0
- Let's pretend this hasn't been released yet - Major overhaul to the health and damage of supermobs - Fixed bug where blazes were doing too much damage - Armor is now far more important than it used to be - Cleaned up the scanner -

Version 1.0.0
- Fixed metadataKiller bug

Version 1.0.0
- Fixed natural mob spawning issue - Fixed loot issue - Completed the switch to level-based mob scaling - Made it so natural mobs mixing with artifical ones results in artificial mobs - Mobs spawned by plugins are now considered natural - Removed stupid attempt at making vanishnopacket compatibility - Improved the visual effects a bit more

Version 1.0.0
- Now cancelling entity explosion damage (due to creeper radius)

Version 1.0.0
- Now properly accounting for invalid commands

Version 0.0.23
- There have been 23 commits pushed to GitHub, so I might as well call this version 23. Not ready for 1.0.0 yet. - Rewrote all of the visual effects, now they support larger amounts of items per track and minor power visual effects stack on the same track while keeping the same distance between them.

Version 0.0.25
- Remembered how to count - Added config options for many, many things, untested so they probably don't work properly yet - Config-related tweaks to the code, which now allows weirder scenarios with entire sections disabled

Version 0.0.26
- Loot is now its own yml file - Added more config options - Tweaked config-related variables - Reworked all commands, fixed miscellaneous bugs in them - Tweaked few settings to fully implement iron golems as aggressive stacking entities

Version 0.0.27
- Fixed iron golem extra stats - Added initial spawnmob command - Last planned features before 1.0.0 are now done, only (possible) bugfixes left before upload

Version 1.0.0
- First public release - Magmasmobs project renamed to EliteMobs - Added a metadata flush method, more organized metadata handling - Fixed fall damage

Version 1.1.0
- Just bug fixes - Fixed level 1 mobs being somewhat unkillable (level 1 mobs aren't supposed to exist anyway) - Fixed gold boots speed power not working - An issue still remains when two manually spawned mobs merge leaving some vestige visual effects behind

Version 1.1.1
- Streamlined minor power making process a bit - Added FireAttack minor power - Fixed ranged mobs not having attack powers

Version 1.1.2
- Added Invisibility minor power

Version 1.1.3
- Added AttackFreeze power

Version 1.1.4
- Added AttackWeb power

Version 1.1.4
- Added BonusLoot power

Version 1.1.5
- Added a way to spawn mobs with specific powers

Version 1.2.0
- Minor code cleanup - Public release of new powers 1.1.x

Version 1.2.1
- Added mob hunting items - Fixed edge case where items would teleport to other worlds (now they just respawn if they have)

Version 1.3.0
- Public release of the features developed during 1.2.x - Few more tweaks for a few edge cases with the freeze power and range attacks

Version 1.3.1
- Added (fabulous) AttackConfusing power - Added InvulnerabilityKnockback power - Reworked parts of the visual effects (particles) - Minor powers now use reflection to add classes to the list (no more manual additions) - Config now partially linked to the metadataHandler so updates always update the config as well - Particle-based effects should now show up for command-spawned mobs

Version 1.3.1
- Added AttackBlinding power - Made AttackConfusing work for ranged elite mobs

Version 1.4.0
- First public version with features added during 1.3.x - Fixed a few config options not being implemented properly (or at all)

Version 1.4.1
- Major code edit/rewrite to adhere more closely to java naming conventions - Probably fixed some minor bug with the loot power - Now using reflection to load listeners for powers, making adding new powers even easier

Version 1.4.2
- Redid all config files so they are more version-independent - Added mobPowers.yml - Nerfed default zombie slaying sword loot, added signature item

Version 1.4.3
- Made it so killing a passive elite mob will make two regular versions of the mob spawn in its place - As such, cancelling mob spawners is no longer necessary, removed that

Version 1.4.4
- Added scoreboard support, permission-based

Version 1.4.5
- Added initial chest GUI elements to the getloot command

Version 1.4.6
- Added tank minorpower

Version 1.4.7
- Added berserker minor power - Past two minor powers are incomplete

Version 1.4.8
- Reduced amount of I/O operations on config files - Reduced amount of reflection operations when scanning for minor powers (big source of slowdown) - Made Tank power mobs have half damage - Made Berserker power mobs half health - Simplified health math - Spawnmob commands now pull from a list of strings, need to find a way to make it non-capitalized - Other miscellaneous minor performance tweaks

Version 2.0.0
- Public release of 1.4.x changes - Ironed out small bug with getloot chest GUI

Version 2.0.1
- Fixed shoddy implementation of damage detection on the DamageHandler, should now only account for valid entities.

Version 2.0.2
- Made it so command blocks should, in theory, be able to use commands to spawn elitemobs natively

Version 2.0.3
- Added Archer MinorPower - Added Fireball MinorPower

Version 2.0.4
- Added the basis to the Taunt MinorPower

Version 2.0.5
- Optimized MinorPower Taunt

Version 2.1
- Public release of 2.0.x changes

Version 2.1.1
- Initial introduction of Major Powers

Version 2.1.2
- Added the ability to fully customize any text displayed to players through translations.yml - Improved the scoreboard aesthetics

Version 2.1.3
- Fixed up config reloading commands - Refactored TeamRocket to ZombieTeamRocket - Tweaks to the ZombieTeamRocket power

Version 2.2.0
- Public release of 2.1.x changes - Added ZombieParents Major Power - Fixed major effects not getting collected - Tweaks to ZombieTeamRocket to prevent its reinforcements from getting powers - Tweaks to scoreboards

Version 2.2.1
- Fixed list of valid powers - Added team rocket death message to config - Added the possibility to get colored lore and item names - Added color code compatibility to everything in the translation config

Version 2.2.2
- Added ZombieFriends power - Fixed minor ZombieParents glitch

Version 2.2.3
- Added ZombieNecronomicon power - Added config option to not use titles to display missing permission messages - Tweaks to existing major powers

Version 2.2.4
- Fixed portal and world-related issues

Version 2.3
- Public release of 2.2.x features

Version 2.3.1
- Fixed null pointer error in necronomicon death event
